            <c altrender="/repositories/10/archival_objects/3558015"
               id="aspace_abdc888385b9949c2dd52650f3370c76"
               level="item">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Letter "To Special Correspondents, Relative to Diseases in Iowa in 1880"</unittitle>
                  <unitdatestructured label="creation" unitdatetype="inclusive">
                     <daterange>
                        <fromdate standarddate="1880">1880</fromdate>
                     </daterange>
                  </unitdatestructured>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_f7ec9846db87e251a6d106680724622d">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Printed circular on blue paper with envelope from L. F. Andrews, Secretary State Board of Health, Des Moines, Iowa. Circular is addressed "to the Correspondents of the State Board of Health" and asks for recipients to submit death and disease statistics to the State Board of Health using the enclosed postage paid envelope.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c altrender="/repositories/10/archival_objects/3558016"
               id="aspace_42867a620016acfdea5dd8387e98e67e"
               level="item">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Letter to Dr Thomas Siveter from the office of Coburn, Birks &amp; Co.</unittitle>
                  <unitdatestructured label="creation" unitdatetype="inclusive">
                     <daterange>
                        <fromdate standarddate="1881">1881</fromdate>
                     </daterange>
                  </unitdatestructured>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_29bac889388d9cc64a777c8b6caf83f9">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>One page written in ink on "Coburn, Birks &amp; Co. wholesale druggists, and dealers in surgical instruments &amp; druggists sundries" letterhead stationary with stamped envelope. "We send you by this mail 1 doz of our catheters, as ordered. We however fail to understand the remainder of your order, please explain more fully and we will send at once."</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
