                     </daterange>
                  </unitdatestructured>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_51d7f17ffc9b03e955ffcaa8d40887e8">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Written in pencil on both sides of one piece of paper. Writer is asking Siveter for assistance in a land dispute.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c altrender="/repositories/10/archival_objects/3558017"
               id="aspace_658e7f0efe131804b4d476a994d75bb7"
               level="item">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Note to Thomas Siveter from Joel James</unittitle>
                  <unitdatestructured label="creation" unitdatetype="inclusive">
                     <daterange>
                        <fromdate standarddate="1882">1882</fromdate>
                     </daterange>
                  </unitdatestructured>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_65ae0033689da648d38135f97197659a">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Short letter written in pencil dated March 23, 1882: "I read your note and in answer would say for you to attend to Campbell immediately. I do no know what is wanted it is all right I expect. Yours, Joel James, Trustee." On reversi is written "Salem Township Trustees Board."</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
